    "\n",
    "# 🏦 Banking Data Analysis & Loan Eligibility Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Leila  \n",
    "**Date:** October 2025\n",
    "\n",
    "## Abstract\n",
    "This notebook analyzes a banking dataset to determine which clients are most likely to be eligible for financing. \n",
    "It combines Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), feature engineering, a supervised learning model (Random Forest), and unsupervised learning (K-Means with PCA visualization). \n",
    "The goal is to provide data-driven insights that align with realistic credit-risk logic.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bf501945",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 1. Problem Statement (Professional)\n",
    "The objective is to identify which banking clients are most likely to be eligible for financing based on their financial data and account activity. \n",
    "This analysis:\n",
    "- Examines client profiles through income, loans, savings, and risk weighting.  \n",
    "- Creates meaningful financial ratios (Debt-to-Income, Assets-to-Loan) to measure financial stability.  \n",
    "- Builds a predictive model (Random Forest) to assess eligibility.  \n",
    "- Applies unsupervised learning (K-Means + PCA) to segment clients and uncover risk/eligibility patterns.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ec7a62d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 2. Setup\n",
    "This section loads packages and the dataset.  \n",
    "> **Note:** Adjust the CSV path if needed.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dddfc649",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, RocCurveDisplay\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "CSV_PATH = \"/mnt/data/banking-clients.csv\"  # change if needed\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(CSV_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "df.head()  # preview\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e9453955",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 3. Data Overview\n",
    "Quick structure, data types, and missing value check.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "99704e5e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "print(\"Shape:\", df.shape)\n",
    "print(\"\\nInfo:\")\n",
    "print(df.info())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nMissing values per column:\")\n",
    "print(df.isna().sum())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "79cef2c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4.1 Numerical distributions\n",
    "We visualize key numeric columns to understand their spread.  \n",
    "*(Using matplotlib as a neutral default for portability.)*\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a85c0af5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "numeric_cols = ['Age', 'Estimated Income', 'Credit Card Balance', 'Bank Loans', \n",
    "                'Bank Deposits', 'Saving Accounts', 'Superannuation Savings',\n",
    "                'Checking Accounts', 'Foreign Currency Account', 'Business Lending']\n",
    "\n",
    "for col in [c for c in numeric_cols if c in df.columns]:\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
    "    plt.hist(df[col].dropna(), bins=30, edgecolor='black')\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Distribution of {col}\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(col); plt.ylabel(\"Count\")\n",
    "    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1c9c2ba2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### 4.2 Categorical frequencies\n",
    "Bar charts for main categorical variables.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d0d9fe05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "categorical_cols = ['Nationality', 'Occupation', 'Fee Structure', 'Loyalty Classification', 'Banking Contact']\n",
    "for col in [c for c in categorical_cols if c in df.columns]:\n",
    "    vc = df[col].value_counts().head(20)  # Top 20 for readability\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))\n",
    "    vc.plot(kind='bar', edgecolor='black')\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Top categories in {col}\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(col); plt.ylabel(\"Count\")\n",
    "    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a2abdf73",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 5. Feature Engineering\n",
    "We create economically meaningful features used throughout the analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **TotalAssets** = Bank Deposits + Saving Accounts + Superannuation Savings  \n",
    "- **TotalDebt** = Bank Loans + Credit Card Balance  \n",
    "- **DebtToIncomeRatio (DTI)** = TotalDebt / (Estimated Income + 1)  *(+1 as a safety)*  \n",
    "- **AssetsToLoansRatio** = (TotalAssets + 1) / (Bank Loans + 1)  *(+1 to avoid division by zero)*\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ebaccf7a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "df['TotalAssets'] = df['Bank Deposits'] + df['Saving Accounts'] + df['Superannuation Savings']\n",
    "df['TotalDebt'] = df['Bank Loans'] + df['Credit Card Balance']\n",
    "df['DebtToIncomeRatio'] = df['TotalDebt'] / (df['Estimated Income'] + 1)\n",
    "df['DebtToIncomeRatio_percent'] = df['DebtToIncomeRatio'] * 100\n",
    "df['AssetsToLoansRatio'] = (df['TotalAssets'] + 1) / (df['Bank Loans'] + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "df[['TotalAssets','TotalDebt','DebtToIncomeRatio','DebtToIncomeRatio_percent','AssetsToLoansRatio']].head()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "095a614b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 6. Correlation Matrix (Numerical)\n",
    "This shows linear relationships between numerical features and helps detect redundancy.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "bfff9f41",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns\n",
    "corr = df[num_cols].corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12,9))\n",
    "plt.imshow(corr, cmap='coolwarm', vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='Correlation')\n",
    "plt.xticks(range(len(num_cols)), num_cols, rotation=90)\n",
    "plt.yticks(range(len(num_cols)), num_cols)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Correlation Matrix (Numerical Features)\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e1f894ae",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 7. Realistic Eligibility Definition\n",
    "We adopt a **multi-criteria rule**, closer to real lending logic:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `DTI < 500%`  \n",
    "- `Risk Weighting ≤ 3`  \n",
    "- `AssetsToLoansRatio > 1.1`  \n",
    "- `Estimated Income > median(Estimated Income)`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4aaa68b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "conditions = (\n",
    "    (df['DebtToIncomeRatio_percent'] < 500) &\n",
    "    (df['Risk Weighting'] <= 3) &\n",
    "    (df['AssetsToLoansRatio'] > 1.1) &\n",
    "    (df['Estimated Income'] > df['Estimated Income'].median())\n",
    ")\n",
    "df['Eligible_realistic'] = conditions.astype(int)\n",
    "df['Eligible_realistic'].value_counts(normalize=True).mul(100).round(2)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c0dc172d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 8. Supervised Learning — Random Forest Classifier\n",
    "We train a Random Forest to predict `Eligible_realistic`.  \n",
    "**Important:** we drop direct leakage variables (`DebtToIncomeRatio`, `DebtToIncomeRatio_percent`).  \n",
    "We keep other variables so the model learns realistic patterns.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a80e88b4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Build X / y\n",
    "drop_ids = ['Client ID','Name']\n",
    "target = 'Eligible_realistic'\n",
    "leak_direct = ['DebtToIncomeRatio','DebtToIncomeRatio_percent']\n",
    "\n",
    "X = df.drop(columns=[c for c in drop_ids + [target] + leak_direct if c in df.columns])\n",
    "y = df[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "# One-hot encode object columns and known ID-like categoricals if they exist\n",
    "obj_cols = X.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()\n",
    "maybe_cats = [c for c in ['BRId','IAId','GenderId','Fee Structure','Loyalty Classification','Banking Contact'] if c in X.columns]\n",
    "for c in maybe_cats:\n",
    "    if c not in obj_cols and c in X.columns:\n",
    "        X[c] = X[c].astype(str)\n",
    "        obj_cols.append(c)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_enc = pd.get_dummies(X, columns=list(set(obj_cols)), drop_first=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train/test split\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X_enc, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train.shape, X_test.shape\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d04a28e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "rf = RandomForestClassifier(\n",
    "    n_estimators=400,\n",
    "    max_depth=None,\n",
    "    min_samples_leaf=2,\n",
    "    class_weight='balanced',\n",
    "    random_state=42,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1\n",
    ")\n",
    "rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "y_pred = rf.predict(X_test)\n",
    "y_proba = rf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Classification report:\\n\", classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\n",
    "print(\"\\nConfusion matrix:\\n\", confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))\n",
    "print(\"\\nROC-AUC:\", round(roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba), 3))\n",
    "\n",
    "RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(rf, X_test, y_test)\n",
    "plt.title(\"ROC Curve — Random Forest (Eligible_realistic)\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "73948d53",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### 8.1 Feature Importance\n",
    "Top factors influencing eligibility predictions.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b9fbfa89",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "importances = pd.Series(rf.feature_importances_, index=X_enc.columns).sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "print(importances.head(20))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
    "importances.head(20).sort_values().plot(kind='barh', edgecolor='black')\n",
    "plt.title('Random Forest Feature Importance (Top 20)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Importance')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c2413a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## 9. Unsupervised Learning — Client Segmentation (K-Means + PCA)\n",
    "We segment clients based on financial features to discover natural profiles.  \n",
    "This helps with risk monitoring and targeted product strategies.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c648d902",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Select features for clustering\n",
    "FEATURES = [\n",
    "    'Estimated Income','TotalDebt','TotalAssets',\n",
    "    'DebtToIncomeRatio','AssetsToLoansRatio','Risk Weighting','Age'\n",
    "]\n",
    "Xc = df[FEATURES].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardize\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "Xs = scaler.fit_transform(Xc)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Elbow & Silhouette to choose k\n",
    "ks = range(2,9)\n",
    "inertias, sils = [], []\n",
    "for k in ks:\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, n_init=20, random_state=42)\n",
    "    km.fit(Xs)\n",
    "    inertias.append(km.inertia_)\n",
    "    sils.append(silhouette_score(Xs, km.labels_))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))\n",
    "plt.subplot(1,2,1)\n",
    "plt.plot(ks, inertias, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Elbow (Inertia)'); plt.xlabel('k'); plt.ylabel('Inertia'); plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(1,2,2)\n",
    "plt.plot(ks, sils, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Silhouette Score'); plt.xlabel('k'); plt.ylabel('Score'); plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "k_best = 4  # <-- adjust after inspecting elbow/silhouette\n",
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k_best, n_init=20, random_state=42)\n",
    "labels = kmeans.fit_predict(Xs)\n",
    "df['Cluster'] = labels\n",
    "\n",
    "# PCA for 2D visualization\n",
    "pca = PCA(n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "X2 = pca.fit_transform(Xs)\n",
    "df['PC1'] = X2[:,0]; df['PC2'] = X2[:,1]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7,6))\n",
    "for c in range(k_best):\n",
    "    mask = (df['Cluster'] == c)\n",
    "    plt.scatter(df.loc[mask,'PC1'], df.loc[mask,'PC2'], s=18, alpha=0.75, label=f'Cluster {c}')\n",
    "plt.title('Client Segmentation — PCA (2D)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('PC1'); plt.ylabel('PC2')\n",
    "plt.legend(); plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "00a0605e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
